386→                        <div id="content">Do all pairs of consecutive <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Powerful_number" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer ugc" target="_blank">powerful numbers</a> $n$ and $n+1$ come from solutions to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pell%27s_equation" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer ugc" target="_blank">Pell equations</a>? In other words, must either $n$ or $n+1$ be a square?<br><br>Is the number of such $n\leq x$ bounded by $(\log x)^{O(1)}$?</div>
